commentTextItems.html: whipped down to fine leg and there's the win, a very comfortable seven wicket margin in the end

commentPostTextItems.html: So few alarms for India in their run chase after a tough start against Blain and Hoffmann. Scotland fought hard all day, especially to recover from 49 for 4 but India had too much class. Gambhir, Uthappa and Yuvraj all spent useful time in the middle ahead of the one-day series and the Indian bowlers put miles in the legs.

India have one more game before the seven-match ODI series, they play the England Lions at Northampton on Saturday, before the first match against England next Tuesday at The Rose Bowl. For now that is all from Cricinfo, from Andrew McGlashan and Andrew Miller thanks for joining us and goodbye.

commentPreTextItems.html: One to win, all the fielders come up to save the single

commentTextItems.html: played down into the gully, Haq prevents the winning run
dropped into the covers "get them in singles"
on middle and played back to Blain
playing away from his body, just wide of backward point who makes a valiant dive as the ball goes to third man
played to square leg, can't get the single so Dravid has a chance to finish the match

commentPreTextItems.html: And here comes the former Scotland batsman Rahul Dravid to hearty applause from the crowd who remember his time here as overseas player

commentTextItems.html: and receives a bouncer first up from Blain, takes Dravid a little by surprise and he was to sway out of the way...welcome back Rahul

doesn't bounce much, Yuvraj goes for another drive but doesn't make contact
cover dives over Yuvraj's back-foot drive and there's enough timing for another boundary
picked off down to long leg
driven on the up straight at extra cover

stories.title: Babies' day out
stories.subTitle: Scotland v India, One-off ODI, Glasgow
stories.summary: India did well to overcome the tough conditions to finish with a crushing win. It was Dravid who struck the winning runs but the youngsters  around him can take heart from a satisfying day out

stories.title: India ease to seven-wicket win
stories.subTitle: Scotland v India, One-off ODI, Glasgow
stories.summary: Scotland recovered from four early blows to reach 203, but a rain-revised target of 209 proved far too easy for India, who improved their on-the-road mark to 6-1
